==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chautauqua
<hw>Chau*tau"qua</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>a meeting, usually held in the
summer outdoors or under a temporary tent, providing public lectures
combined with entertainment such as concerts and plays. It originated in
the village of Chautauqua, N. Y., in 1874, and was popular in the late
19th and early 20th centuries. Also, a meeting similar to
this.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

